			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard songs AE agro for raid.  IS this true or a myth?<a name="58796"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 24 04 11:47 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Sirioh is absolutely correct.  I will see if I can explain it a little differently...
<br />

<br />
When a player FD pulls, or a Bard uses Fading Memories, they are dumping aggro to get rid of the target mob's &quot;helpers&quot;.  The adds originally came, because they were within the target mob's &quot;help radius&quot;, or the mob's pathing crosses their &quot;help radius&quot; and they add.  (Privided those mobs were not lulled.)
<br />

<br />
When the player FDs or FMs, all aggro is wiped.  They wait for the adds to be farther away from the target mob, then retag the target mob to single pull them.
<br />

<br />
Here is how the Bard gets aggro with AE songs:
<br />

<br />
The monk is running back with a train of mobs, all aggrod on the Monk.  The AE Bard's song lands on the monk, so the Bard gets the same kind of aggro that a healer would, if they healed him right then.  The Bard &quot;helped&quot;.  When the Monk FDs to dump aggro, the mobs go to the next person on the hate list... THE BARD who &quot;helped&quot; him.
<br />

<br />
It is standard practice for Bards to stop all AE songs, (and group songs, if they are grouped with the puller) when they do the pull.  If the mob is a Rampaging mob, then the Bard should also wait for the Rampage list to be established before singing AE songs again.  If resists MUST be on the MT upon engagement, then you need several Bards, cause the first one is probably gonna die, lol.
<br />

<br />
As for the song ITSELF cause aggro?  NOPE.  If you start Chorus of Marr, get invised by somone (don't start a new song or invis drops, hehe) and go stand RIGHT NEXT TO a non-see-invis mob, you can target it, /poke, /smack, /rude all day, and that mob will not aggro, though you were bathing the whole room with CoM.  
<br />

<br />
The song itself does not cause aggro.  The song landing on the puller and transferring aggro just like healing transfers aggro, causes the train.
<br />

<br />
Don't sing until the single mob arrives.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
