				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard songs AE agro for raid.  IS this true or a myth?<a name="58798"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 24 04 12:09 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It can be a timing issue, too.  There is no guarantee you WILL get agro if a monk moves into song range and then feigns.  If FD goes off successfully before the song pulses within agro range, you won't necessarily get chain agro.  Songs hitting an already feigned monk won't get agro either.  What WILL get agro is of the song pulses on the monk within agro radius of his pull before the monk fiegns.  I am routinely in the tag/support position for a monk puller for Code raids.  You simply plan on turning off songs when the monk heads out to make the next pull.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
