				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard songs AE agro for raid.  IS this true or a myth?<a name="59294"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 27 04 11:09 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Look, this isn't that hard to do folks.
<br />

<br />
The duration of Elemental Chorus (for example) is 2-3 ticks or 12 to 18 seconds.  Trust me -- I am not some supremely gifted twitch gamer with lightning reflexes in real life, but even I can plan a 5 to 7 second window as a mob approaches and have the resist buff on the raid, song turned off, and not hit it again until after the main tank engages and keep resists on people the entire time.  It requires a bit of timing and anticipation, but if I can do it, I'm sure 90% of you all can, too.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=443370">Steppy Astravox</a><br>
Code of Silence<br>
Luclin Server</span></td>
