			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard songs AE agro for raid.  IS this true or a myth?<a name="59978"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 1 04 3:43 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>caliopeia said it all...
<br />
Know your range.
<br />

<br />
When the puller is close turn off songs.  As already stated songs last 18 seconds.  So you can sing it once before the monk is in range... then pump it again after the raid engages.    
<br />

<br />
I do not worry much about rampage... just make sure you have a hot key setup for FM and if any of your songs pulse before MT/RT engage just hit it quickly.  Actually I like to hit FM 2-3 times during Boss fights just to make sure I am one of the last ones to die.    I guess this all depends on your FT though and how fast your raid pulls.
<br />

<br />
Also keep in mind rampage has a small range... so when everyone first engages you can sit out for a few seconds before using FM.     The minimal dps we provide will not make or break the kill.
<br />

<br />
One last note... if you are in MT group... you will want them songs on the MT when he engages.  The first few seconds are the most important (some unslowed mobs are just mean).  So be ready to FM very early in the fight and again soon after to make sure you are on the bottom of the list.  In addition you may want to not melee and just use instruments to enhance your buffs.  You may die a few times at first... not all MT are the same so you might have to adjust your timing/song order.  
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
